[src:representation-theory/representation-theory-of-finite-groups-p01] Two representations $(\rho ,V_{\rho }),(\pi ,V_{\pi })$ are called **equivalent** or **isomorphic**, if there exists a G –linear vector space isomorphism between the representation spaces.
