[src:representation-theory/representation-theory-of-finite-groups-p01] A representation $(\pi ,V_{\pi })$ is called **faithful** when $\pi$ is injective.
[src:representation-theory/representation-theory-of-finite-groups-p01] A representation is called **semisimple** or **completely reducible** if it can be written as a direct sum of irreducible representations.
