[src:representation-theory/representation-theory-of-finite-groups-p02] Induction theorems relate the representation ring of a given finite group *G* to representation rings of a family *X* consisting of some subsets *H* of *G*.
[src:representation-theory/representation-theory-of-finite-groups-p02] ; induction theorems give criteria for the surjectivity of this map or closely related ones.
